The paper focuses on learning vector-space embeddings for multi-relational data, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of lexical resources, which are commonly used in NLP, supporting the likelihood of cs.CL. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach for initializing relational models, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates its approach on a dataset, which is relevant to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
